---
description: Sage Search Skill — research best practices for this stack and write them as team skills
alwaysApply: false
---

When asked to run **sage-search-skill** or "research skills for this project":

Scan this project's stack and domains, research current best practices and
trending patterns relevant to it, then write the findings as reusable skill
entries under `agents/sage/`. Run this once when starting on a new repo, or
whenever the team wants a knowledge refresh.

1. **Map the project.** Read root config files (`package.json`, `pyproject.toml`,
   etc.) and a sample of source files. Identify the stack, framework(s), domains
   (folder structure / feature areas), and what's already in `agents/sage/`.

2. **Research current best practices** for this exact stack. Use web search if
   available. Focus on: UI/component patterns, minimal code (YAGNI, SRP),
   code quality, performance, and patterns trending in the last 12 months.
   Prefer specific, opinionated guidance over generic advice.

3. **Write skill entries** to `agents/sage/<domain>/skills/<slug>.md`:
   ```markdown
   ---
   id: <slug>
   type: skill
   title: <short title>
   domain: <domain>
   status: proposed
   source: ai
   enforcement: advise
   tags: [<tag>, ...]
   ---

   <one-paragraph explanation — what, why, when>

   **Do:** concrete example
   **Avoid:** anti-pattern
   ```
   One idea per file. Never duplicate existing entries. Update stale ones in place.

4. **Report** what was written. The dev reviews and flips `status: approved`.
